subsection.p:
Electric force \vec F_e between two charges q_1 and q_2 separated by a distance r has the following magnitude and direction.
\amp \text{Magnitude:}\ \ F_e\propto \frac{|q_1| |q_2|}{r^2}. \amp \text{Direction: use the rule: like charges repel, opposite charges attract.}
The direction of the force on any one of the charges depends on the type of the two charges and the charge on which the force acts as shown in .

solution.p:
We will use the formula for the magnitude of the Coulomb force. Note that we strip the sign when we just need the magnitude.

	 F_e \amp = k \dfrac{q_1 q_2}{r^2}
	 \amp = 9 \times 10^9 \dfrac{1.60 \times 10^{-19} \times 1.60 \times 10^{-19}}{(5.3 \times 10^{−11})^2}
	 \amp = 8.2 \times 10^{-8}\text{ N}.
